Sec. 143.123. REQUIRING REMOVAL OF FENCE BY ANOTHER PERSON. A
person who is the owner of a fence that is wholly on that person's
land may require the owner of an attached fence to disconnect and
withdraw the attached fence by giving six months' notice of the
required disconnection. The notice must be in writing and given to
the owner of the attached fence or that person's agent, attorney, or
lessee.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1351, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

